Note:
==============================================================================
IEEE 754-2008 binary256 (octuple precision) software implementation
==============================================================================

Format (256 bits):
  bit 255       : sign
  bits 254-236  : exponent (19 bits, bias 262143)
  bits 235-0    : mantissa fraction (236 bits, implicit leading 1)

Internal representation: 32-byte arena-allocated buffer addressed by pointer.
Layout: little-endian across four 64-bit words.
  byte offsets [0..7]   = limb0 (mantissa bits 0..63)
  byte offsets [8..15]  = limb1 (mantissa bits 64..127)
  byte offsets [16..23] = limb2 (mantissa bits 128..191)
  byte offsets [24..31] = limb3 (mantissa bits 192..235 + exponent + sign)

We chose flat-buffer over struct-of-fields for the same reason as binary128:
byte-pattern interop with binary I/O, plus a clean fit with arena allocation.

Internal arithmetic for multiplication requires 512-bit intermediate values,
carried as eight 64-bit limbs.

References:
  IEEE 754-2008 § 3.7 (extended-precision formats)
  binary256 has no published canonical KAT suite; we validate via
  cross-consistency tests (a+b = c => c-b = a, etc.) and against
  representative values from numerical analysis literature.
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as Memory
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/bitwise_core.runa" as Bits
Import "runtime/core/memory/arena.runa" as Arena

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Format constants
Note: ============================================================================

Constant F256_BITS as Integer is 256
Constant F256_EXP_BITS as Integer is 19
Constant F256_MANT_BITS as Integer is 236
Constant F256_BIAS as Integer is 262143
Constant F256_EXP_MAX as Integer is 524287
Constant F256_BYTES as Integer is 32

Note: Within limb3 (top 64-bit word):
Note:   bit 63       = sign
Note:   bits 62..44  = exponent (19 bits)
Note:   bits 43..0   = top 44 bits of mantissa
Constant F256_SIGN_MASK_LIMB3 as Integer is -9223372036854775808
Constant F256_EXP_MASK_LIMB3 as Integer is 9223090561878065152
Constant F256_MANT_MASK_LIMB3 as Integer is 17592186044415
Constant F256_HIDDEN_BIT_LIMB3 as Integer is 17592186044416

Constant ROUND_NEAREST_EVEN as Integer is 0
Constant ROUND_TOWARD_ZERO as Integer is 1
Constant ROUND_TOWARD_POSITIVE as Integer is 2
Constant ROUND_TOWARD_NEGATIVE as Integer is 3

Constant FLAG_INVALID as Integer is 1
Constant FLAG_DIVIDE_BY_ZERO as Integer is 2
Constant FLAG_OVERFLOW as Integer is 4
Constant FLAG_UNDERFLOW as Integer is 8
Constant FLAG_INEXACT as Integer is 16

Let F256_ROUNDING_MODE be 0
Let F256_EXCEPTION_FLAGS be 0

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Allocation + raw limb access
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "f256_alloc" takes arena as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Allocate and zero-initialize a 32-byte Float256.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    arena_allocate + memory_fill 0.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    One arena bump + 32-byte zero.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Zero is +0.0, a valid Float256.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let p be proc arena_allocate from Arena with arena, F256_BYTES
    If p is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_fill from Memory with p, 0, F256_BYTES
    Return p
End Process

Process called "f256_get_limb" takes p as Integer, idx as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Read the idx-th 64-bit limb (idx in [0..3]).
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Single 64-bit load at offset idx*8.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    One load.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Caller responsibility to keep idx in [0..3].
    @End Security_Scope
    Let off be idx multiplied by 8
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with p, off
End Process

Process called "f256_set_limb" takes p as Integer, idx as Integer, value as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Write the idx-th 64-bit limb.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Single 64-bit store at offset idx*8.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    One store.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Caller responsibility for idx.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let off be idx multiplied by 8
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with p, off, value
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Field access
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "f256_get_sign" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Sign bit is bit 63 of limb3.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Load limb3, shift right by 63, mask 1.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    One load + two ALU.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let limb3 be proc f256_get_limb with p, 3
    Let shifted be limb3 shifted right by 63
    Return shifted bitwise and 1
End Process

Process called "f256_get_exponent" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Exponent occupies bits 62..44 of limb3 (19 bits, biased).
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Shift limb3 right by 44, mask with 0x7FFFF (524287).
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    One load + two ALU.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let limb3 be proc f256_get_limb with p, 3
    Let shifted be limb3 shifted right by 44
    Return shifted bitwise and F256_EXP_MAX
End Process

Process called "f256_get_mantissa_top44" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    The top 44 bits of the 236-bit mantissa occupy bits 43..0 of limb3.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Load limb3, AND with mask of low 44 bits.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    One load + one ALU.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let limb3 be proc f256_get_limb with p, 3
    Return limb3 bitwise and F256_MANT_MASK_LIMB3
End Process

Process called "f256_set_fields" takes p as Integer, sign as Integer, biased_exp as Integer, mant_top44 as Integer, mant_mid64 as Integer, mant_lower64 as Integer, mant_bottom64 as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Compose sign + exponent + 236-bit mantissa into limb3..limb0.
    mant_top44 = bits 192..235 (top 44 bits of the fraction part);
    mant_mid64 = bits 128..191; mant_lower64 = bits 64..127;
    mant_bottom64 = bits 0..63.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Defensive masking on each field, shifts, ORs.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Constant time.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Caller-owned buffer.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let s be sign bitwise and 1
    Let e be biased_exp bitwise and F256_EXP_MAX
    Let mt be mant_top44 bitwise and F256_MANT_MASK_LIMB3
    Let limb3 be s shifted left by 63
    Let e_shifted be e shifted left by 44
    Set limb3 to limb3 bitwise or e_shifted
    Set limb3 to limb3 bitwise or mt
    proc f256_set_limb with p, 3, limb3
    proc f256_set_limb with p, 2, mant_mid64
    proc f256_set_limb with p, 1, mant_lower64
    proc f256_set_limb with p, 0, mant_bottom64
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Classification
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "f256_is_zero" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    All bits except sign are zero.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Check each limb.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Four loads + four branches.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let l3 be proc f256_get_limb with p, 3
    Let l3_no_sign be l3 bitwise and 9223372036854775807
    If l3_no_sign is not equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let l2 be proc f256_get_limb with p, 2
    If l2 is not equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let l1 be proc f256_get_limb with p, 1
    If l1 is not equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let l0 be proc f256_get_limb with p, 0
    If l0 is not equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "f256_is_inf" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Exponent == max AND mantissa == 0.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Check exponent then mantissa limbs.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Constant time.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let exp be proc f256_get_exponent with p
    If exp is not equal to F256_EXP_MAX:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let mt be proc f256_get_mantissa_top44 with p
    If mt is not equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let l2 be proc f256_get_limb with p, 2
    If l2 is not equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let l1 be proc f256_get_limb with p, 1
    If l1 is not equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let l0 be proc f256_get_limb with p, 0
    If l0 is not equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "f256_is_nan" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Exponent == max AND mantissa != 0.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Check exponent then any mantissa limb nonzero.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Constant time.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let exp be proc f256_get_exponent with p
    If exp is not equal to F256_EXP_MAX:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let mt be proc f256_get_mantissa_top44 with p
    If mt is not equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let l2 be proc f256_get_limb with p, 2
    If l2 is not equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let l1 be proc f256_get_limb with p, 1
    If l1 is not equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let l0 be proc f256_get_limb with p, 0
    If l0 is not equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "f256_is_signaling_nan" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    NaN with mantissa MSB (bit 235) clear. Bit 235 of mantissa is bit 43
    of limb3 (the high mantissa-portion word).
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Reject non-NaN, then check bit 43 of limb3.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    A few branches.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let nan be proc f256_is_nan with p
    If nan is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let mt be proc f256_get_mantissa_top44 with p
    Let msb_mask be 8796093022208
    If (mt bitwise and msb_mask) is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "f256_is_subnormal" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Exponent == 0 AND mantissa != 0.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Test exponent then mantissa.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Few branches.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let exp be proc f256_get_exponent with p
    If exp is not equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let mt be proc f256_get_mantissa_top44 with p
    If mt is not equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let l2 be proc f256_get_limb with p, 2
    If l2 is not equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let l1 be proc f256_get_limb with p, 1
    If l1 is not equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let l0 be proc f256_get_limb with p, 0
    If l0 is not equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "f256_is_normal" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    0 < exponent < max.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Range check.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    One load + two branches.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let exp be proc f256_get_exponent with p
    If exp is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If exp is equal to F256_EXP_MAX:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "f256_is_finite" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Exponent != max.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Single comparison.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    One load + one branch.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let exp be proc f256_get_exponent with p
    If exp is equal to F256_EXP_MAX:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "f256_is_negative" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Sign bit is set.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Read sign bit.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Constant time.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure.
    @End Security_Scope
    Return proc f256_get_sign with p
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Rounding + flags
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "f256_set_rounding_mode" takes mode as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Switch the active rounding mode.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Range-checked store.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Constant time.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Module-global.
    @End Security_Scope
    If mode is less than 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If mode is greater than 3:
        Return 0
    End If
    Set F256_ROUNDING_MODE to mode
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "f256_get_rounding_mode" returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Read.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Load.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    One load.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Read-only.
    @End Security_Scope
    Return F256_ROUNDING_MODE
End Process

Process called "f256_raise_flag" takes flag as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Sticky OR.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    OR + store.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Constant time.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Module-global.
    @End Security_Scope
    Set F256_EXCEPTION_FLAGS to F256_EXCEPTION_FLAGS bitwise or flag
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "f256_clear_flags" returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Reset sticky register.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Store 0.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Constant time.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Module-global.
    @End Security_Scope
    Set F256_EXCEPTION_FLAGS to 0
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "f256_get_flags" returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Snapshot.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Load.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    One load.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Read-only.
    @End Security_Scope
    Return F256_EXCEPTION_FLAGS
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Special constructors
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "f256_make_zero" takes arena as Integer, sign as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    ±0.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Alloc + optional sign bit.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Constant time.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Arena-owned.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let p be proc f256_alloc with arena
    If p is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If sign is equal to 1:
        proc f256_set_limb with p, 3, F256_SIGN_MASK_LIMB3
    End If
    Return p
End Process

Process called "f256_make_inf" takes arena as Integer, sign as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    ±Inf.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Place exponent_max in limb3 with optional sign.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Constant time.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Arena-owned.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let p be proc f256_alloc with arena
    If p is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let l3 be F256_EXP_MAX shifted left by 44
    If sign is equal to 1:
        Set l3 to l3 bitwise or F256_SIGN_MASK_LIMB3
    End If
    proc f256_set_limb with p, 3, l3
    Return p
End Process

Process called "f256_make_qnan" takes arena as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Canonical quiet NaN: exp=max, mantissa MSB=1.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Alloc + write limb3.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Constant time.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Arena-owned.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let p be proc f256_alloc with arena
    If p is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let exp_part be F256_EXP_MAX shifted left by 44
    Let quiet_bit be 8796093022208
    Let l3 be exp_part bitwise or quiet_bit
    proc f256_set_limb with p, 3, l3
    Return p
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Internal multi-limb arithmetic (256-bit unsigned)
Note: ============================================================================
Note: All helpers operate on 4-limb tuples (limb0, limb1, limb2, limb3) with
Note: limb0 holding the low-order 64 bits. Output is via 4 caller-provided
Note: 8-byte buffer pointers.
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "f256_add256" takes a0 as Integer, a1 as Integer, a2 as Integer, a3 as Integer, b0 as Integer, b1 as Integer, b2 as Integer, b3 as Integer, out0 as Integer, out1 as Integer, out2 as Integer, out3 as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Sum two 256-bit unsigned values held as (limb0, limb1, limb2, limb3).
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Limb-by-limb add with carry propagation. Detect unsigned carry via
    the standard "carry iff (a&b)|((a|b)&~sum) has bit 63 set" pattern.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Four adds + a few branches.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure; caller-owned output pointers.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let s0 be a0 plus b0
    Let and_lo be a0 bitwise and b0
    Let or_lo be a0 bitwise or b0
    Let not_s0 be bitwise not s0
    Let inner_lo be or_lo bitwise and not_s0
    Let cm0 be and_lo bitwise or inner_lo
    Let cm0_shift be cm0 shifted right by 63
    Let c0 be cm0_shift bitwise and 1

    Let s1_raw be a1 plus b1
    Let s1 be s1_raw plus c0
    Note: carry from a1+b1+c0: detect via two-step.
    Let and1 be a1 bitwise and b1
    Let or1 be a1 bitwise or b1
    Let not_s1r be bitwise not s1_raw
    Let inner1 be or1 bitwise and not_s1r
    Let cm1a be and1 bitwise or inner1
    Let c1a be (cm1a shifted right by 63) bitwise and 1
    Note: also carry if s1_raw + c0 wrapped (only possible when s1_raw == -1)
    Let c1b be 0
    If c0 is equal to 1:
        If s1_raw is equal to -1:
            Set c1b to 1
        End If
    End If
    Let c1 be c1a bitwise or c1b

    Let s2_raw be a2 plus b2
    Let s2 be s2_raw plus c1
    Let and2 be a2 bitwise and b2
    Let or2 be a2 bitwise or b2
    Let not_s2r be bitwise not s2_raw
    Let inner2 be or2 bitwise and not_s2r
    Let cm2a be and2 bitwise or inner2
    Let c2a be (cm2a shifted right by 63) bitwise and 1
    Let c2b be 0
    If c1 is equal to 1:
        If s2_raw is equal to -1:
            Set c2b to 1
        End If
    End If
    Let c2 be c2a bitwise or c2b

    Let s3_raw be a3 plus b3
    Let s3 be s3_raw plus c2

    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with out0, 0, s0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with out1, 0, s1
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with out2, 0, s2
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with out3, 0, s3
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "f256_sub256" takes a0 as Integer, a1 as Integer, a2 as Integer, a3 as Integer, b0 as Integer, b1 as Integer, b2 as Integer, b3 as Integer, out0 as Integer, out1 as Integer, out2 as Integer, out3 as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    a - b assuming a >= b.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Limb-by-limb subtract with borrow propagation.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Four subs + branches.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let d0 be a0 minus b0
    Let not_a0 be bitwise not a0
    Let and_b0 be not_a0 bitwise and b0
    Let or_b0 be not_a0 bitwise or b0
    Let inner_b0 be or_b0 bitwise and d0
    Let bm0 be and_b0 bitwise or inner_b0
    Let bm0_shift be bm0 shifted right by 63
    Let bo0 be bm0_shift bitwise and 1

    Let d1_raw be a1 minus b1
    Let d1 be d1_raw minus bo0
    Let not_a1 be bitwise not a1
    Let and_b1 be not_a1 bitwise and b1
    Let or_b1 be not_a1 bitwise or b1
    Let inner_b1 be or_b1 bitwise and d1_raw
    Let bm1a be and_b1 bitwise or inner_b1
    Let bo1a be (bm1a shifted right by 63) bitwise and 1
    Let bo1b be 0
    If bo0 is equal to 1:
        If d1_raw is equal to 0:
            Set bo1b to 1
        End If
    End If
    Let bo1 be bo1a bitwise or bo1b

    Let d2_raw be a2 minus b2
    Let d2 be d2_raw minus bo1
    Let not_a2 be bitwise not a2
    Let and_b2 be not_a2 bitwise and b2
    Let or_b2 be not_a2 bitwise or b2
    Let inner_b2 be or_b2 bitwise and d2_raw
    Let bm2a be and_b2 bitwise or inner_b2
    Let bo2a be (bm2a shifted right by 63) bitwise and 1
    Let bo2b be 0
    If bo1 is equal to 1:
        If d2_raw is equal to 0:
            Set bo2b to 1
        End If
    End If
    Let bo2 be bo2a bitwise or bo2b

    Let d3 be a3 minus b3
    Set d3 to d3 minus bo2

    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with out0, 0, d0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with out1, 0, d1
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with out2, 0, d2
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with out3, 0, d3
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "f256_compare256" takes a0 as Integer, a1 as Integer, a2 as Integer, a3 as Integer, b0 as Integer, b1 as Integer, b2 as Integer, b3 as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Unsigned compare on 256-bit tuple.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Compare from high limb to low, treating each as unsigned via sign-flip XOR.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    A few branches.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let a3_u be a3 bitwise xor F256_SIGN_MASK_LIMB3
    Let b3_u be b3 bitwise xor F256_SIGN_MASK_LIMB3
    If a3_u is less than b3_u:
        Return -1
    End If
    If a3_u is greater than b3_u:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let a2_u be a2 bitwise xor F256_SIGN_MASK_LIMB3
    Let b2_u be b2 bitwise xor F256_SIGN_MASK_LIMB3
    If a2_u is less than b2_u:
        Return -1
    End If
    If a2_u is greater than b2_u:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let a1_u be a1 bitwise xor F256_SIGN_MASK_LIMB3
    Let b1_u be b1 bitwise xor F256_SIGN_MASK_LIMB3
    If a1_u is less than b1_u:
        Return -1
    End If
    If a1_u is greater than b1_u:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let a0_u be a0 bitwise xor F256_SIGN_MASK_LIMB3
    Let b0_u be b0 bitwise xor F256_SIGN_MASK_LIMB3
    If a0_u is less than b0_u:
